{title: Hark, the Vesper Hymn Is Stealing - 58}

{start_of_verse}
Hark! the vesper hymn is stealing
O’er the waters soft and clear;
Jubilate, Jubilate, Jubilate,
Amen.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse}
Nearer yet, and nearer pealing,
Soft it breaks upon the ear.
Jubilate, Jubilate, Jubilate,
Amen.
{end_of_verse}